/* Install instructions the pairwise repo
	 Author: Manodeep Sinha <manodeep@gmail.com>
	 Bugs: Please email me
	 Date: At some point in early 2015
*/

Steps:

1. Edit the common.mk file to select the appropriate use-case

Options are:
				a) SQRT_DIST: Distances calculated will be square-rooted (disabled by default)
				b) COLORED_OUTPUT: Output messages will be colored (enabled by default)
				c) USE_MKL: Use the Intel Math Kernel Library for BLAS (disabled by default)

2. Set the compiler in common.mk -- icc/gcc/clang are supported. 

3. Type make to create all the executables


